Project Overview

GMAccS: GPU-Accelerated Secondary Genomic Analysis
GMAccS is a cutting-edge technology designed to accelerate secondary genomic analysis using GPU accelerators. This project integrates an in-house developed genome aligner, seamlessly connected with GATK (Genome Analysis Toolkit), to create a comprehensive genomic analysis pipeline.

Key Features

Complete Pipeline: Incorporates sequencing alignment and variant calling.
GPU Acceleration: Utilizes GPU platforms to achieve high-performance parallel processing.
Integration with GATK: Ensures compatibility with industry-standard genomic tools.

We will perform benchmarking on small and large genomes to evaluate the performance of the pipeline. The analysis will cover various design spaces to conduct a thorough Design Space Exploration (DSE).

